config.userPrompt:
Analyze this search request and create an optimized search plan with 2-3 parallel query variants.

User's Question: {{state.data.searchQuery}}
Today's Date: {{state.data.currentDate}}

Respond with this JSON structure:
{
  "classification": {
    "realtime": true/false,
    "temporal": "today|this_week|this_month|this_year|historical|timeless",
    "domain": "sports|news|tech|science|finance|health|entertainment|general",
    "intent": "score_lookup|news|how_to|fact_check|price_check|weather|comparison|general_info",
    "entities": ["entity1", "entity2"]
  },
  "queries": [
    {
      "query": "optimized search string",
      "dateRestrict": "d1",
      "siteSearch": "espn.com",
      "exactTerms": "Chiefs"
    }
  ]
}

RULES:
- Generate 2-3 queries approaching from different angles
- Each query: 3-8 words, optimized for Google (no question marks, no filler)
- For time-sensitive queries: include the date in at least one query, use dateRestrict (d1=past day, w1=past week, m1=past month, y1=past year)
- siteSearch: target authoritative domains (sports→espn.com, news→reuters.com, tech→arstechnica.com, finance→bloomberg.com)
- exactTerms: specific names/entities that MUST appear
- One query should be broad, one narrow/specific, one from an alternative angle
- dateRestrict, siteSearch, exactTerms are all optional per query — only include when they add value
